def average_col_by_rounds(df, column_name):
    df[[column_name]] = np.divide(df[[column_name]].values, np.add(df[['offense_rounds_won']].values, df[['defense_rounds_won']].values))
    return df

# create a LinearRegression model
model = LinearRegression()

# fit the model using the year and temperature data
X = top_100_most_played[['offense_result']]
y = top_100_most_played[['game_result']]
model.fit(X.values, y.values)

# create a list of years between 1940 and 2020
x_range = np.arange(np.min(X.values), np.max(X.values), step=.01)
x_range = x_range.reshape(-1, 1)
# Create figure with one subplot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 7))
# use the model to predict the average annual temperature for each year
predicted_temps = model.predict(x_range.reshape(-1, 1))
# plot the predicted temperatures on top of the scatterplot
plt.scatter(top_100_most_played['offense_result'], top_100_most_played['game_result'], label='Data')
plt.plot(x_range, predicted_temps, color = 'red', label='Regression Line')
fig.suptitle('Offense Winrate and Game Winrate', fontsize=18)
plt.xlabel('Offense Half Winrate', fontsize=13)
plt.ylabel('Game Winrate', fontsize=13)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
params = model.coef_
print(params)
